    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-02-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="645" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 645.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to
                            Mr. <persName type="to">Wallace</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-02-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 27,
                            1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 268.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        466, of the 24th ultimo, reporting conversations with the minister of
                        foreign affairs and the grand vizier respecting the proposed new treaty of
                        commerce between Turkey and the United States.</p>
                <p>This Government is as much interested as Turkey in removing all causes of
                        misapprehension, and if it will benefit our pending reclamations you may
                        assure the Porte of the good disposition of this Government.</p>
                <p>Further report will, however, be awaited before definitely instructing you to
                        make a new tariff and treaty.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
